# WHAT IT IS
#   `ipget` is "wget for IPFS" — the official IPFS Project CLI for
#   retrieving an IPFS path (CID, /ipfs/, /ipns/, /ipld/, http://,
#   https://, or bare hash) and saving it to the local filesystem.
#   It can run in four node-acquisition strategies:  connect to an
#   already-running local IPFS daemon, spawn an in-process node
#   from an existing IPFS repo, spawn an in-process node in a
#   throwaway temp repo, or "fallback" (try local, then spawn).
#   The retrieval streams content through the `boxo/files` Unixfs
#   abstraction, preserves directory layouts on disk, and
#   optionally renders a progress bar via cheggaaa/pb.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from main.go `cli.Command`
#                       struct — urfave/cli/v3 v3.8.0)
#   ipget [OPTIONS] <IPFS_OBJECT> [<IPFS_OBJECT>...]
#
#   Options:
#     -o, --output <PATH>            Output location (file or
#                                    directory).  Defaults to the
#                                    final path segment of the
#                                    object.
#     -n, --node <STRATEGY>          IPFS node acquisition strategy
#                                    [local|spawn|temp|fallback —
#                                    default: fallback]
#                                    local    → connect to running
#                                              IPFS daemon
#                                    spawn    → in-process node
#                                              using existing repo
#                                              (falls back to
#                                              "temp" if no repo)
#                                    temp     → in-process node
#                                              using a temp repo
#                                              cleaned up on exit
#                                    fallback → try local, then
#                                              spawn
#     -p, --peers <PEER>...          IPFS peers to connect to
#                                    (repeatable; comma-separated
#                                    accepted)
#     --progress                     Show a progress bar during
#                                    download
#
#   Object argument forms accepted:
#     <CID>                          Bare base32/base58 CID
#     /ipfs/<CID>[/<PATH>]           Standard /ipfs/ path
#     /ipns/<NAME>[/<PATH>]          IPNS path
#     /ipld/<CID>[/<PATH>]           IPLD path
#     ipfs://<CID>[/<PATH>]          URL scheme form (ipld:// also
#                                    accepted via parsePath)
#     ipns://<NAME>[/<PATH>]
#     http[s]://<GATEWAY>/<PATH>     Gateway URL — path component
#                                    becomes the IPFS path
#
#   Standard urfave/cli auto-flags:
#     -h, --help                     Show help
#     -v, --version                  Show version
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   Direct dependency on `github.com/libp2p/go-libp2p v0.48.0`
#   declared in go.mod — the canonical Go libp2p implementation
#   maintained by the libp2p project (libp2p/go-libp2p).
#   go-libp2p is THE Go peer-to-peer networking stack:  it
#   provides the `host.Host` interface, `network.Network`,
#   `peer.AddrInfo`, the `peerstore`, transports (TCP, QUIC,
#   WebSocket, WebTransport, memory), upgrades (TLS / Noise),
#   multiplexers (yamux, mplex), the protocol-buffer codec, the
#   `routing.PeerRouting` interface, and the Kademlia DHT
#   (`libp2p/go-libp2p-kad-dht`) used by IPFS for content / peer
#   routing.  ipget's `node.go` builds a libp2p `Host` via
#   `kubo/core/coreiface.CoreAPI`, joins the IPFS DHT swarm, and
#   resolves the requested CID through `Unixfs().Get(ctx,
#   iPath)` — the entire fetch happens over go-libp2p streams.
#   The transitive go.mod also pins go-libp2p-kad-dht v0.39.1,
#   go-libp2p-pubsub v0.15.0, go-libp2p-record v0.3.1, and the
#   full Kubo HTTP/DHT/routing helper stack.  Verified via:
#     gh api repos/ipfs/ipget/contents/go.mod
#       → github.com/libp2p/go-libp2p v0.48.0
#       → github.com/urfave/cli/v3 v3.8.0
#       → module github.com/ipfs/ipget
#     gh api repos/ipfs/ipget/contents/main.go
#       → cmd := &cli.Command{Name: "ipget",
#           Usage: "Retrieve and save IPFS objects.", ...
#           Flags: [output, node, peers, progress]}
#   This entry is the Go=140 leader bump (round-number R930 commit
#   landmark) that continues Axis 85 (P2P / libp2p Networking
#   Stack) opened at R929 with Rust=rust-libp2p via enbop/fungi.
#
#   No completion for `ipget` ships with Apple zsh
#   (/usr/share/zsh/*/functions) or Homebrew zsh-completions
#   (/opt/homebrew/share/zsh/site-functions) — confirmed absent.
# ============================================================================

_ipget() {
    _arguments -s \
        '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[show help]' \
        '(- *)'{-v,--version}'[show version]' \
        '(-o --output)'{-o,--output}'=[output location]:path:_files' \
        '(-n --node)'{-n,--node}'=[IPFS node strategy]:strategy:(local spawn temp fallback)' \
        '*'{-p,--peers}'=[IPFS peer to connect to (repeatable)]:peer:' \
        '--progress[show a progress bar]' \
        '*:IPFS object (CID, /ipfs/<cid>, /ipns/<name>, ipfs\://<cid>, https\://<gateway>/<path>):'
}

_ipget "$@"
